cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the monitoring of global-scale online data and the spread of information in a social network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the use of data and network structure, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). The paper also uses data analysis techniques, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses privacy considerations and cyber threats, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
